==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*hlaiba-'', from Indo-European ''*kel-, *klei-''.  Cognate with Old High German [[hleib]] (German [[Laib]]), Old Norse [[hleifr]] (Old Swedish ''lēver''), Gothic [[𐌷𐌻𐌰𐌹𐍆𐍃]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[κλίβανος]] ‘baking oven’, Old Slavic ''chlěb’'' (Russian [[хлеб]] ‘bread’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /hla:f/

===Noun===
'''hlāf''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''hlāfas''')
# [[bread]]
